{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"89741927-f0a5-47ef-b15a-5aa0d82360a6","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n**1. Update/add NuGet packages:**\n```xml\n<!-- Remove or keep NUnit3TestAdapter, but update to ≥ 4.6.0 (you already have this) -->\n<!-- Add the MTP adapter: -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit.Extension.MicrosoftTestingPlatform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\n**2. Enable the platform** in your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformSupport>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests with:**\n```bash\ndotnet test          # works as before\n# or run the test executable directly:\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` is still needed.\n- `NUnit3TestAdapter` (≥ 4.6.0) is still needed — it bridges NUnit to the new platform.\n- The `NUnit.Extension.MicrosoftTestingPlatform` package wires up the new entry point.\n- After migration, the test binary becomes a standalone executable, so you can also run it directly (`./YourTests`).\n\nNo test code changes are required — only the project file and package references.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"95013df9-055e-4764-9c9c-983cc2d99807","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question - I don't need to look at any files. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":400,"requestId":"BD0B:EF7A9:1C8D141:20394F2:6A07C429"},"id":"4223b8a5-159c-4300-8dff-a3ad47dbe7cf","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:11:15.718Z","parentId":"a7d8f9a5-2026-4e0a-af8a-e13f5329d526"}
